re proper rendering of styled blocks, tables, and code snippets. The rules emphasize compatibility with Tistory's editor auto-conversion while maintaining professional presentation of technical content.","sessionId":"ses_0c4f2c32fffeHj6r5a9OeIWnFl","subtitle":"AI technology blog posting standards for Tistory platform","timestamp":"2026-07-07T05:29:25.705Z","title":"Read tistory blog writing rules","type":"file_read"},"obs_mra7lq7l_e7798eb88fc9":{"concepts":["blog content strategy","AI news curation","fact-checking protocols","search engine optimization keywords","open source software advocacy","LLM model coverage","MCP server ecosystem"],"confidence":1,"facts":["File path: /home/rg3270/blog/deer-flow-backup/shared/BLOG_SETTINGS.md","26 fixed search keywords covering LLMs (DeepSeek, Mistral, Llama, Grok, GPT, Perplexity), Korean/Chinese AI (KT SK LG AI, Z.ai, GLM-5, MiniMax, Qwen, KIMI), tools (Antigravity, Claude Code, Ollama, OpenClaw, Opencode, MCP), and applications","Blog name: James AI Explorer, category: tech blog (AI tools, coding agents, MCP servers, local AI), author: Atlas (Korean)","Writing criteria: practicality (step-by-step guides), free/open source priority, catchy titles with emojis, news within 7 days only, profitability focus","Recent posts list from 2026-03-27 to 2026-04-04 covering Gemma 4, GLM-5V-Turbo, Qwen3.6 Plus, Claude Code leaks, Hermes Agent, JEPA, TurboQuant, AI-Scientist-v2, GLM-5.1, OpenClaw vs Claude Code, Nemotron-Cascade-2","System instructions: load keywords every new thread, avoid asking for keywords, check recent posts to avoid duplicate topics, search news using the 26 keywords","Fact-checking rules (tightened after Post 884 incident): verify all numbers/benchmarks against original articles, confirm CVE numbers in NVD, obtain at least 3 independent sources, exclude unverifiable figures"],"files":["/home/rg3270/blog/deer-flow-backup/shared/BLOG_SETTINGS.md"],"id":"obs_mra7lq7l_e7798eb88fc9","importance":7,"narrative":"Read the pe